name: Isuru Gayan Dasanayake
title: Automation Engineer
description: I am a dynamic and energetic engineer eagerly waiting to contribute my skills and talents at my best for any challenging task either in academic or industrial community. A communicative, encouraging team player who presents ideas effectively, proactively and is able to assist others in the latest procedures.

about.text: I am a dedicated engineer with extensive experience in industrial automation, project management, and research. My expertise spans across PLC programming, SCADA systems, robotics, and mechatronics. I have successfully led multiple automation projects and teams, delivering innovative solutions to complex industrial challenges.  With a strong background in both academic research and industrial applications, I bring a unique perspective to engineering problems. My work has been recognized through awards and publications in prestigious journals.  I am passionate about continuous learning and staying updated with the latest technological advancements in the field of automation and engineering.

projects.title: Siemens PLC Machine Control Panel
projects.description: This project involved the complete design and deployment of an advanced Siemens PLC-based control panel system for a beverage manufacturing company in Thailand. The project began with understanding the clients production workflow and converting those requirements into electrical and automation designs. The control logic was developed using Siemens TIA Portal, ensuring precise control over motors, conveyors, heaters, and safety devices. HMI screens were created to give operators full visibility, including alarm history, production statistics, and machine status. The panel was manufactured with strict adherence to industrial standards, including proper cable routing, component selection, and safety interlocks. After fabrication, on-site commissioning included I/O testing, calibration, simulation-based verification, and final operational testing with the production line. The final solution improved machine reliability, minimized downtime, and increased production output.
